io.odysz.transact.sql.parts

Class ExtFileInsert

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.odysz.transact.sql.parts.AbsPart
      • io.odysz.transact.sql.parts.ExtFileInsert

  • public class ExtFileInsert
extends AbsPart
    External file representation - mapping URI and file path back and forth.
    An ExtFile can only been used as a setting value in update/insert statement.

    This class is only used for update and insert. For reading, use Funcall.extFile(String)

    Note

    The sql(ISemantext) method can be only used as insert mode. The DASemantics.ShExtFile only place this class in insert statement.
    Author:
    odys-z@github.com

      • ExtFileInsert

        public ExtFileInsert(Resulving fn,
                     String configRoot,
                     ISemantext stx)
        Set the absolute root path. This path is used to access file together with the relative path set by ExtFileInsert#prefixPath(String).
        The argument doesn't have to be absolute path if the runtime can access a file from a relative path.
        But servlet containers needing absolute paths to access file, so this must been set to the absolute path, such as the return of javax.servlet.ServletContext#getRealPath(String).
        Parameters:
        fn - file name to be resolved
        configRoot - root path in config.xml
        stx - instance of run time context
